narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: The Complete business of Hollywood. Seriously. Professor Johnson does an incredible job of moving through the eras of Hollywood from its origins to its modern day status with excellent detail and just the right amount of complexity. You will also gain insight into the box office and be able to articulate the factors that determine a movies success or ultimate failure.
This course is incredibly insightful and teaches a lot about the film business and its inner workings. There's also a lot of interesting history discussed!
The understanding of Hollywood history, the modern movie industry and how studios work.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The strengths are the level of depth for each topic. Professor Johnson always provided additional materials for particularly curious students but also ensured that everyone was able to discuss the topics at hand at a formidable level.

The strengths of this course are its focus on present-day events and its interesting final project. The course's main weakness was that some of the readings didn't always seem relevant, but given that the course is shifting due to changes with COVID, it's understandable!

Strengths: the very detailed and complete introduction of the movie industry. The introduction of Hollywood integrated its history, adjustment and latest news. 

Weaknesses: Open discussion was few.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! This is a great course for film majors and non-majors alike.
I would recommend this to anyone who is interested in understanding the film industry in more detail! It's super insightful.
Yes. The course was a very good opportunity to learn Hollywood.
